FaqQuestion.create!(id: 1, title: "Doesn't everyone in your chapter talk, dress and act the same?", content: '<p>We pride ourselves on the fact that we are different. That is what holds us together. There is no single characteristic that makes us Phi Taus. You cant say "Phi Tau, they are all jocks" or "Phi Tau, they only care about school". We do a little bit of everything and do it well. We have Brothers from all over the nation and from all different majors, races, and creeds. We are all different and we like it that way.</p>', faq_category_id: 1, order: 1)
FaqQuestion.create!(id: 2, title: 'Isnt that a lot of money for dues?', content: '<p>Dues are $450 a semester. At first glance, that may seem like a lot, but when we break it down, you can see where the money is going. Some of the money goes into insurance provided by our National Organization. If anything happens to any of us while with the fraternity, we are covered. Some of the money funds our events. When we have dinners every other week or social events with sororities, we dont charge for attendance. You can think of it as prepaying for your weekend activities. The rest of the money goes towards items that are beneficial for the entire house, such as furniture, TVs, paper towels, and Brotherhood dinners.</p>', faq_category_id: 1, order: 2)
FaqQuestion.create!(id: 3, title: 'What are the advantages of fraternity membership?', content: '<p>In a nutshell, Phi Tau helps with time management, scholarship, athletics, philanthropy, community service, social experience, job placement, and friendly connections. You become a member of a 80,000 man organization nation-wide, and a 500+ man organization here at RIT.</p>', faq_category_id: 1, order: 3)
FaqQuestion.create!(id: 4, title: 'What is Phi Kappa Tau doing about alcohol and substance abuse?', content: '<p>By focusing its efforts on character building, Phi Kappa Tau hopes to equip brothers to make healthy and intelligent choices for themselves and others. Phi Tau is addressing alcohol abuse at the core of the issue by providing its men with the skills and knowledge needed to make responsible decisions. When brothers make unwise choices, Phi Tau holds them accountable at the chapter and national level.</p>', faq_category_id: 1, order: 4)
FaqQuestion.create!(id: 5, title: 'How does Phi Kappa Tau rank compared to other Fraternities?', content: '<p>Ranking Phi Kappa Tau, or any fraternity for that matter, depends on any number of variables. Typically, the question begs to the issue of how many chapters the organization has and/or how many alumni are on the record books with good addresses. There are presently 66 mens social fraternities that are members of the North-American Inter fraternity Conference. In terms of numbers of active chapters and total living alumni, Phi Kappa Tau ranks in the top 25 of the NIC member groups.</p>', faq_category_id: 2, order: 1)
FaqQuestion.create!(id: 6, title: 'How would you describe the other fraternities here on campus?', content: '<p>We respect every other house on campus. The best way to explain it is that if you value academics, athletics, leadership, philanthropy, community service, and social life, you should be Greek. What house you belong in is a different story. Every house has a different personality. We all share the same goals and visions - we just have different personalities. If you think you fit in at our house then you may be Phi Tau material and we would love to have you here, but there is no way to know until you check out the other houses. variables. Typically, the question begs to the issue of how many chapters the organization has and/or how many alumni are on the record books with good addresses. There are presently 66 mens social fraternities that are members of the North-American Inter fraternity Conference. In terms of numbers of active chapters and total living alumni, Phi Kappa Tau ranks in the top 25 of the NIC member groups.</p>', faq_category_id: 2, order: 1)
